consignment /kənˈsaɪnmənt/

(consignments) 

1. N-COUNT A consignment of goods is a load that is being delivered to a place or person. (货物) 批 

例： The first consignment of food was flown in yesterday. 第一批食品昨天空运到了。 

2. PHRASE If goods are sold on consignment , the owner is given a percentage of the price once they are sold. 以代售方式 

例： She sold clothes on consignment to benefit homeless people. 她以代售方式卖服装来施益于无家可归的人。

